text: West Friesland or Westfriesland can refer to the following: *West Friesland (region), a contemporary region in the province of North Holland, Netherlands *The same region as the State of West Friesland in the Dutch Republic *Occasionally, the region where the West Frisian language is spoken, i.e., mostly the province of Friesland in the Netherlands *West Frisia, the western part of the historical region of Frisia *Westfriesland, a Dutch ship of the line of 78/80 guns of the Admiralty of the Noorderkwartier, built in c.1666 *Wsetfriesland, a Dutch ship of the line of 90 guns of the Admiralty of the Noorderkwartier, built in 1682.
title: West Friesland
